    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the highly sought-after 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary powerplant. This specimen exhibits flawless mechanical topography; the sequential boost transition is seamless, and recent compression testing confirms the apex seals are well within factory tolerances. The chassis retains its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension geometry and aluminum arms, providing the telepathic feedback and 50/50 weight distribution synonymous with this platform. Power is delivered through a precise five-speed manual transmission to a Torsen limited-slip differential. Every vacuum line, bushing, and cooling component has been meticulously inspected to ensure thermal efficiency and boost stability. This is a rare, unmodified example in concours-level condition, free of the typical heat-cycling wear found in the engine bay.",
